From: Paulo Alcantara <pc@manguebit.com>
Date: Tue, 2 Apr 2024 16:33:58 -0300
Subject: [PATCH] smb: client: fix potential UAF in smb2_is_valid_lease_break()
References: bsc#1218260
Patch-mainline: 6.6.26
Git-commit: 705c76fbf726c7a2f6ff9143d4013b18daaaebf1

commit 705c76fbf726c7a2f6ff9143d4013b18daaaebf1 upstream.

Skip sessions that are being teared down (status == SES_EXITING) to
avoid UAF.

Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
Signed-off-by: Paulo Alcantara (Red Hat) <pc@manguebit.com>
Signed-off-by: Steve French <stfrench@microsoft.com>
Signed-off-by: Greg Kroah-Hartman <gregkh@linuxfoundation.org>
Signed-off-by: Robert Frohl <rfrohl@suse.com>
---
 fs/smb/client/smb2misc.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/fs/smb/client/smb2misc.c b/fs/smb/client/smb2misc.c
index 3f4c37458f97..cc72be5a93a9 100644
--- a/fs/smb/client/smb2misc.c
+++ b/fs/smb/client/smb2misc.c
@@ -622,6 +622,8 @@ smb2_is_valid_lease_break(char *buffer, struct TCP_Server_Info *server)
 	/* look up tcon based on tid & uid */
 	spin_lock(&cifs_tcp_ses_lock);
 	list_for_each_entry(ses, &pserver->smb_ses_list, smb_ses_list) {
+		if (cifs_ses_exiting(ses))
+			continue;
 		list_for_each_entry(tcon, &ses->tcon_list, tcon_list) {
 			spin_lock(&tcon->open_file_lock);
 			cifs_stats_inc(
